# Optional: full URL of the Nest API (no trailing slash).
# ─ Local dev (`npm run dev`): leave unset — requests go to /api and Vite proxies → http://127.0.0.1:3001
# ─ `vite preview` on localhost: same as dev (unset + proxy). Start the backend on port 3001.
# ─ Deployed SPA with API elsewhere: SET at build time, e.g. VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com

# Backend must be running for the dashboard: `cd plos-backend && npm run start:dev`.
# Empty accounts get `[PLOS seed]` dummy responsibilities from the API (see `dashboard-dummy-seed.ts`).
# Disable with DISABLE_DASHBOARD_DUMMY_SEED on the backend if you prefer a truly blank dashboard.

# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3001

# Optional analytics / monitoring (leave unset locally)
# VITE_POSTHOG_KEY=
# VITE_POSTHOG_HOST=https://app.posthog.com
# VITE_SENTRY_DSN=
